We have a situation where all of a sudden the Nav Map macro includes previous versions of some pages, so we have the same page on the list 4-6 times...

Links are also differentiated in that normal links are {code} "{site}/display/{space}/{page}" {code}
but the "extra links" are of format: {code} "{site}/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=xxxxx" {code}
(I assume this is just the normal way to fetch a specific version)...

This is not the case for all pages though.

Unfortunately since it just suddenly had some extra pages, there is no deterministic way to reproduce this at this moment, I will try to push forward for index rebuilds or updates, but I am not the one managing our confluence installation here so it will take some time to get feedback from that.

